ERAL NEI CHATTI CHORU !!! 
BEGUM’s KITCHEN SERIES - Episode 15.

I remember how much we cherished fighting over the chatti choru while growing up. To me, it’s truly the heart of any dish made at home, filled with memories and love as my ammi would make small balls of the leftover masala n feed us 🥹🥹🥹, ahhhhhh good old days right???

Eral chatti choru hits different cos the rice, ghee, masala combo is BANG ON when it comes to prawns n can never go wrong. Guess what? This recipe is incredibly simple, making it the perfect choice for anyone—whether you’re a bachelor, a spinster, or a busy working mom/ dad, look no further as this banger straightforward recipe is for YOU,

South Indian Lunch !!!
7 days, 7 super simple ideas. 

While growing up, we enjoyed simple South Indian food with a Muslim twist, which has influenced the way I prepare food today. Its a great mix of veggies with some much needed authentic dakhani Muslim non vegetarian dishes n trust me its soul satisfying n absolutely delicious. I have been getting tonnessssss of requests to convert my thaali stories into a REEL so its helpful for so many women out there who struggle with the Q “Whats for lunch today ?”. Thank me later...

Day 1 : Rice, Sorakkai Kootu (Bottle gourd) , Egg fry, Mutton lal masala, Papad.
Day 2 : Ghee rice, Vegetable curry (Carrot, Beans, Potatoes) , Chicken fry. 
Day 3 : Rice, Yellow Dal with Sorakkai (Bottle gourd) , Sirikeerai Poriyal (Spinach) , Fish fry.
Day 4 : Rice, Sambar (Drumstick, Yellow Pumpin, Kathrikai, Raw mango), Chicken Kerala fry, Beetroot poriyal, Raw banana fry.
Day 5 : Rice, Ghee, Arbi Salna (Taro root), Mutton Shaami Kebab, Cabbage poriyal, Raw mango pickle.
Day 6 : Tamarind rice, Kovakkai fry (Ivy Gourd), Mutton Phal (peppery masala), Wheel chips.
Day 7 : Lemon rice, Masala vadai, Prawn roast, Vendakkai poriyal (ladys finger).

COMMENT IF YOU WANT A PART 2. 

SAVE THIS REEL & SHARE IT WITH YOUR POOKIE.
PRO TIP : Simply take a print out, stick it in your fridge for NO BRAINER LUNCH IDEAs.

TOP 3 BUDGET FRIENDLY NEW BRANDS AT BESSY !!! 
#notsponsored 

It’s the WEEKEND, n I’m back to give you an update on all the happening NEW BUDGET FRIENDLY FOOD SPOTS in Besant Nagar Beach . Now do SHARE THIS REEL & make a beach plan for this weekend n ENJOYYYYY !!! 

1. TIN TIN @tintin.icecreams , it’s the same place where KIMCHI used to be … TIN TIN is all about icecreams n cold coffee in cute cans. 

2. FRYDAY @fryday_burgers , they r all about the yummiest beef burgers , Nashville chicken burgers and loaded fries. Very similar to Soul, Crave kinda burger spots . Do try their smashed beef burgers & Nashville burger it’s yummmm. 

3. Marina Sandys @marina_sandyskitchen , located inside the lane next to Popeyes , they are all about budget friendly very local beach kinds noodles , fried rice and starters. Total VALUE FOR MONEY. 

SAVE FOR LATER !!!

CAFE LOVERS UNITE!!! 
#notsponsored 

Ok now WHO’s GUILTY???? Huh... 
By now, you all know this is exactly how I run when I find a new Coffe spot & trust me we spend a lot of time researching, shooting & editing info about new COFFEE spots in #chennai. Here are my 2 new finds ; 

1. Southside Cafe & Community @southsidecafechennai, neatly tucked away in a quiet lane after VGP in ECR before Bay 6, is this super aesthetic new cafe, its not too crowded n has a beautiful outdoor area so I'd say a perfect place to work, chill n relax. 
PRO TIP : Have your late lunch n do a coffee takeout, walk to the beach with your loved ones n chill. 

2. SORTED, Alwarpet. This brand new spot has gained traction cos of their superb location. They have amazing coffee,  banger food, an event space and a work space as well. However, their official launch is June 1st week so I'd say wait it out for a few more weeks before visiting them.

TURNING 41 AT MY FAVV CAFE !!! 
@themayflowerchennai 

What better way than to celebrate my birthday with a “MEET & GREET “ session with my amazing followers at the newly opened @themayflowerchennai in Velachery . They had organised the most amazing HI TEA with a banger menu filled with the yummiest snacks , coffee , chai & a hot choc worthy of those extra calories , if you know what I mean 🤪❤️😍

I was overwhelmed with emotion meeting everyone. I truly can’t thank my followers and the entire team at MAYFLOWER CAFE enough for their incredible hospitality. The way they hosted us was absolutely beautiful, and it really meant a lot to me. Birthday feels guaranteed ❤️❤️❤️

The HI TEA menu was absolutely fantastic! The best part? You can CREATE YOUR OWN Hi tea with all the delicious snacks you love. You have to try their desserts—they're so amazing that we all took some home to satisfy those late-night cravings!

Thank you n Bon Appetite.

TOP 3 BIRIYANI !!! #chennai 

Biryani is an emotion, Biryani is BAE, Biryani is everything in life nu if you feel, then this reel is for YOU. On that note, let’s discuss newer Briyani spots I found this year ; 

1. PRAWN BIRYANI - ₹100 - MAATHA BIRYANI - They serve the yummiest prawn Biriyani in town & also have Seeragasamba rice mutton biryani which is super delicious. Their chic thokku n chic 65 side dishes alongside these biryani is a combo one cannot miss. Address - New Avadi Road, Kilpauk. Call - 9551219494

2. BEEF NALLI BIRYANI - ₹80 - They excel in juicy beef Nalli biryani with beef fry side dish. I was informed that they can make mutton biryani on order basis. Absolutely loved the taste and the juicy Nalli pieces. Address - NOORANI HOT & SPICY - No.1, Nyniappa Maistry St, Royapettah. 
Call Ahmed - 63806 30973

3. BIRYANI PAYANAM @biryanipayanam - A brand new cloud kitchen that specialises in CHICKEN biryani made with the finest ingredients. Do try them out for party orders / corporate orders, totally worth it.
